owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setAvatar(address).details: Sets the avatar to a new avatar (`newAvatar`).

setTarget(address).details: Sets the target to a new target (`newTarget`).

setUp(bytes).details: Initialize function, will be triggered when a new proxy is deployed

params.amountIn: The amount of tokenIn to sell (for event logging)
params.augustusCalldata: The raw calldata from Velora API to execute on Augustus
params.augustusSwapper: The Velora Augustus Swapper contract address
params.minAmountOut: The minimum amount of tokenOut to receive (slippage protection)
params.receiver: The address that receives swap output (must be whitelisted)

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

getGovernanceAddress().notice: Get the address of the proto DAO. Override to use Zodiac Module's ownership mechanism.

getInternalVersion().notice: Track version during internal development. We bump up when new whitelistings added.

isAllowedAsset(address).notice: Are we allowed to trade/own an ERC-20.

performCall(address,bytes).notice: Keep backward compatibility with the old performCall

performCall(address,bytes,uint256).notice: The main entry point for the trade executor. - Checks for the whitelisted sender (=trade executor hot wallet) - Check for the allowed callsites/token whitelists/etc. - Execute transaction on behalf of Safe

setAvatar(address).notice: Can only be called by the current owner.

setTarget(address).notice: Can only be called by the current owner.

swapAndValidateVelora(address,address,ad.notice: Execute a Velora (ParaSwap) swap through the Safe. Unlike CowSwap which uses offchain order books and presigning, Velora executes atomically by calling Augustus Swapper directly. Validation is consolidated in VeloraLib to minimise the module's bytecode (EIP-170).

validateCall(address,address,bytes).notice: Revert if the smart contract call is not allowed

whitelistERC4626(address,string).notice: Whitelist an ERC-4626/ERC-7540 vault. - Callsites for deposits and redemptions - Vault share and denomination tokens - Any ERC-4626 extensions are not supported by this function, like special share tokens - ERC-4626 withdrawal address must be always the Safe - Because of non-standardisation the whitelisted function list is long
